Capitol Bikeshare Project

Dependencies

1. Python - http://www.python.org
2. Django - http://www.djangoproject.com/
3. PostgreSQL - http://www.postgresql.org/
4. Apache - http://httpd.apache.org/
5. Psycopg - http://initd.org/psycopg/
6. Python-openid - http://pypi.python.org/pypi/python-openid/
7. Python-oauth2 - https://github.com/simplegeo/python-oauth2
8. Django Social Auth - http://social.matiasaguirre.net/

Notes:

For PostgreSQL, it's recommended that you create your own user login
(other than the default postgres user).  You must allow that user to
connect to the database from localhost.  You can do that editing the
file /etc/postgresql/8.4/main/pg_hba.conf.  If the PostgreSQL user you
created for this project was 'myuser', the file would look like this:

# Database administrative login by UNIX sockets
local   all         postgres                          ident

# TYPE  DATABASE    USER        CIDR-ADDRESS          METHOD

# "local" is for Unix domain socket connections only
local   all         myuser                            md5
local   all         all                               ident
# IPv4 local connections:
host    all         all         127.0.0.1/32          md5
# IPv6 local connections:
host    all         all         ::1/128               md5



Installation:

1. Check out the project from github.com

$ git clone git@github.com:ajhinz/Bikeshare-project.git

2. Edit the settings.py file in the bike_project directory.  You must
set the database name, user, and password.

3. Create the database objects

$ cd Bikeshare-project
$ ./manage.py syncdb

4. Create the apache site that points to this project by adding the
following to /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/000-default


        WSGIScriptAlias / /usr/local/django/Bikeshare-project/apache2/django.wsgi
        <Directory /usr/local/django/Bikeshare-project/apache2>
                Order deny,allow
                Allow from all
        </Directory>

        Alias /static /usr/local/django/Bikeshare-project/static
        <Directory /usr/local/django/Bikehsare-project/static>
                Order deny,allow
                Allow from all
        </Directory>

        Alias /media /usr/lib/pymodules/python2.6/django/contrib/admin/media
        <Directory /usr/lib/pymodules/python2.6/django/contrib/admin/media>
                   Order deny,allow
                   Allow from all
        </Directory>


5. (Re)Start Apache

$ sudo service apache2 restart
